35
[p 
	"If this is your first time encoding, you'll need the following software
	[a id=r1 
	]a
	[sup 
		"[
		[a href=#1 
			"1
		]a
		"]
	]sup
	", roughly in the order you will need it:
	$LF
]p
[ol 
	[li 
		" The means to create a distinctive 
		[a href=/EncodingGuide/Logo 
			"logo
		]a
		" for the encode (this is usually image editing software such as 
		[a class=extlink href=http://www.gimp.org/ rel=nofollow 
			"Gimp
		]a
		" or 
		[a class=extlink href=http://www.getpaint.net/ rel=nofollow 
			"Paint.NET
		]a
		" for Windows users).
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" The ability to play back the site's input files.  See 
		(__wikiLink|Emulator Resources)
		" for information on where to obtain the emulators used.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" For Windows-centric emulators, a lossless (preferably RGB) VFW codec. For a comparison between several codecs that fit the need, see 
		[a href=/forum/viewtopic.php?t=12390 
			"this forum thread
		]a
		". Most commonly used right now are:
		$LF
		[ol 
			[li 
				" The 
				[a class=extlink href=http://sourceforge.net/projects/camstudio/files/legacy/ rel=nofollow 
					"CamStudio codec
				]a
				";
				$LF
			]li
			[li 
				" The 
				[a class=extlink href=http://lags.leetcode.net/codec.html rel=nofollow 
					"Lagarith (LAGS) codec
				]a
				";
				$LF
			]li
		]ol
		" One of the following (sets of) software packages:
		$LF
		[ol 
			[li 
				" 
				[a class=extlink href=http://www.mplayerhq.hu/ rel=nofollow 
					"mplayer/mencoder
				]a
				", a popular and powerful media player and encoding suite; or
				$LF
			]li
			[li 
				" For Windows users, 
				[a class=extlink href=http://www.avisynth.org/ rel=nofollow 
					"AVISynth
				]a
				" (in particular, the scripts in use in this guide require a 
				[a class=extlink href=http://sourceforge.net/projects/avisynth2/files/AviSynth_Alpha_Releases/ rel=nofollow 
					"2.6.x alpha
				]a
				"; 
				[a class=extlink href=http://avisynth.org/mediawiki/Syntax_Highlighting rel=nofollow 
					"different
				]a
				" AviSynth syntax highlighters are very useful as well; for 
				[b 
					"Notepad++
				]b
				" get 
				[a class=extlink href=http://code.google.com/p/feos-tas/downloads/detail?name=userDefineLang.xml rel=nofollow 
					"this one
				]a
				") and 
				[a class=extlink href=http://www.virtualdub.org/ rel=nofollow 
					"VirtualDub
				]a
				".
				$LF
				[ul 
					[li 
						" The AVISynth scripts presented here employ duplicate frame removal through the 
						[a href=/forum/viewtopic.php?t=12065 
							"ExactDedup plugin
						]a
						" (note that there are some external dependencies presented at the bottom of that page).
						$LF
					]li
				]ul
			]li
		]ol
		" 
		[a class=extlink href=http://komisar.gin.by/ rel=nofollow 
			"x264
		]a
		", the site's standard software for heavy duty video encoding - Windows builds are available, for example, 
		[a class=extlink href=http://komisar.gin.by/ rel=nofollow 
			"here
		]a
		". List of available parameters is 
		[a class=extlink href=http://mewiki.project357.com/wiki/X264_Settings rel=nofollow 
			"here
		]a
		".
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Audio encoding software; the site normally uses
		$LF
		[ol 
			[li 
				" 
				[a class=extlink href=http://www.geocities.jp/aoyoume/aotuv/ rel=nofollow 
					"aoTuV
				]a
				", for vorbis audio (not generally compatible with MP4 containers); or
				$LF
			]li
			[li 
				" 
				[a class=extlink href=http://www.nero.com/eng/downloads-nerodigital-nero-aac-codec.php rel=nofollow 
					"Nero AAC Codec
				]a
				" (builds for both Windows and Linux), for AAC audio; or
				$LF
			]li
			[li 
				" 
				[a class=extlink href=https://sites.google.com/site/qaacpage/ rel=nofollow 
					"qaac
				]a
				" 
				$LF
			]li
		]ol
		" 
		[a class=extlink href=http://sox.sourceforge.net/ rel=nofollow 
			"SoX
		]a
		", for removing a delay from audio tracks introduced during the encoding process (AAC audio only)
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" An audio/video multiplexer (muxer); either
		$LF
		[ol 
			[li 
				" mkvmerge from 
				[a class=extlink href=http://www.bunkus.org/videotools/mkvtoolnix/ rel=nofollow 
					"mkvtoolnix
				]a
				", for muxing to MKV; or
				$LF
			]li
			[li 
				" 
				[a class=extlink href=http://www.videohelp.com/tools/mp4box rel=nofollow 
					"MP4Box
				]a
				", part of the 
				[a class=extlink href=http://gpac.sourceforge.net/ rel=nofollow 
					"GPAC
				]a
				" project, for muxing to MP4.
				$LF
			]li
		]ol
		"Having a relatively recent desktop computer is recommended for the sake of encoding speed, but not absolutely required.
		$LF
	]li
]ol
[p 
	"Configuration of this software will be addressed during the rest of the guide as it is needed.
	$LF
]p
[hr 
]hr
[p 
	"Next page: 
	[a href=/EncodingGuide/Logo 
		"Logo
	]a
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"[
	[a id=1 
	]a
	[a href=#r1 
		"1
	]a
	"]
	": Packages for most of these pieces of software are available for most Linux distributions; instructions for how to install them from there will be omitted.
]p
